# 🚀 AWS Route 53 Multi-Region Failover Architecture — Setup Guide

This guide explains how to deploy a highly available multi-region failover architecture using AWS Route 53, EC2, and Application Load Balancers.

---

# 📌 Project Objective

Build a production-style architecture where:

- Users access the application using a domain name
- Route 53 monitors server health
- Traffic automatically switches to a backup region if the primary region fails

---

# 🏗️ Architecture Overview

```text
Users
   │
   ▼
Amazon Route 53
   │
   ├──────────────► Primary Region (Mumbai)
   │                    │
   │                    ▼
   │              Application Load Balancer
   │                    │
   │                    ▼
   │                 EC2 Server
   │
   └──────────────► Secondary Region (Singapore)
                        │
                        ▼
                 Application Load Balancer
                        │
                        ▼
                    Backup EC2
```

---

# 🛠️ AWS Services Used

| Service | Purpose |
|---|---|
| Route 53 | DNS and Failover Routing |
| EC2 | Web Hosting |
