# ⚙️ Prerequisites

Before starting:

✅ AWS Account  
✅ Domain Name (Optional)  
✅ Basic AWS Knowledge  
✅ IAM User with Administrator Access  

---

# 🔥 Step 1 — Launch Primary EC2 Instance

## Region

```text
ap-south-1 (Mumbai)
```

---

## EC2 Configuration

| Setting | Value |
|---|---|
| AMI | Amazon Linux 2 |
| Instance Type | t2.micro |
| Security Group | Allow HTTP and SSH |

---

## Install Apache

Connect to EC2 and run:

```bash
sudo yum update -y
sudo yum install httpd -y
sudo systemctl start httpd
sudo systemctl enable httpd
```

---

## Create Web Page

```bash
echo "Primary Server Running" | sudo tee /var/www/html/index.html
```

---

# 🔥 Step 2 — Launch Backup EC2 Instance

## Region

```text
ap-southeast-1 (Singapore)
```

---

## Install Apache

```bash
sudo yum update -y
sudo yum install httpd -y
sudo systemctl start httpd
sudo systemctl enable httpd
```

---

## Create Backup Web Page

```bash
echo "Backup Server Running" | sudo tee /var/www/html/index.html
```

---

# 🔥 Step 3 — Create Target Groups

Create target groups in both regions.

---

## Configuration

| Setting | Value |
|---|---|
| Target Type | Instances |
| Protocol | HTTP |
| Port | 80 |

---

# 🔥 Step 4 — Register EC2 Instances

Attach:

- Primary EC2 → Primary Target Group
- Backup EC2 → Backup Target Group

---

# 🔥 Step 5 — Create Application Load Balancers

Create:

- Primary ALB (Mumbai)
- Secondary ALB (Singapore)

---

## ALB Configuration

| Setting | Value |
|---|---|
| Scheme | Internet Facing |
| Listener | HTTP : 80 |

---

# 🔥 Step 6 — Test ALB

Copy ALB DNS name and open in browser.

Expected:

```text
Primary Server Running
```

and

```text
Backup Server Running
```

---

# 🔥 Step 7 — Open Route 53

Go to AWS Console.

Search:

```text
Route 53
```

---

# 🔥 Step 8 — Create Hosted Zone

Click:

```text
Hosted Zones
```

Then:

```text
Create Hosted Zone
```

---

## Configuration

| Setting | Value |
|---|---|
| Domain Name | example.com |
| Type | Public Hosted Zone |

---

# 🔥 Step 9 — Create Health Check

Go to:

```text
Health Checks
```

Click:

```text
Create Health Check
```

---

## Health Check Configuration

| Setting | Value |
|---|---|
| Endpoint | Primary ALB DNS |
| Protocol | HTTP |
| Port | 80 |

---

# 🔥 Step 10 — Create Failover Records

---

# Primary Record

| Setting | Value |
|---|---|
| Record Type | A |
| Alias | Yes |
| Route Traffic To | Primary ALB |
| Failover | Primary |
| Health Check | Attach Created Health Check |

---

# Secondary Record

| Setting | Value |
|---|---|
| Record Type | A |
| Alias | Yes |
| Route Traffic To | Secondary ALB |
| Failover | Secondary |

---

# 🔥 Step 11 — Testing

Open domain name in browser.

Expected Output:

```text
Primary Server Running
```

---

# 🔥 Step 12 — Simulate Failure

Stop primary EC2 instance.

Wait for Route 53 health check failure.

Refresh website.

Expected Output:

```text
Backup Server Running
```

Traffic automatically redirects to backup region.

